gy and biblical studies forward. The turn to scripture, as a source for theological and philosophical reflection, marks an important advance for the recent "theological turn" in phenomenology. At the same time, by bringing to light the incredible complexity of scripture, phenomenology provides a ay for contemporary biblical studies to exceed its own limits. Wells demonstrates how phenomenology and scripture ultimately illuminate one another in profound and surprising ways.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aIncarnation. 0aPhenomenology. 0aPhilosophical theology. 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Paul's Letters.2bisacsh1 aHart, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2018z978311149142440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847218840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438472188423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438472188/original  a978-3-11-149142-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles